    "long_instructions": "## Do This\r\n\r\n1. In your `custom.py` file create a function called `paint_and_move()` that repeatedly paints a square and moves forward.\r\n    - Hint: Use a `while painter.has_paint()` to make the `Painter` keep painting until it runs out of paint. \r\n2. Use the `paint_and_move()` function inside a loop to paint a path until the `Painter` runs out of paint.\r\n     - Hint: Create a function that uses `while painter.is_on_bucket()` to collect multiple buckets of paint at once.\r\n    - Hint: Remember to use the `turn_left()` and `can_move` `Painter` methods and your  `turn_right()` function as needed.\r\n    \r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n",
